"\"Those isles are compass’d by the Ionian main; The dire abode where the foul Harpies reign, Forc'd by the winged warriors to repair To their old homes, and leave their costly fare. Monsters more fierce offended heaven ne’er sent From hell’s abyss, for human punishment— With virgin-faces, but with wombs obscene, Foul paunches, and with ordure still unclean ; § With claws for hands, and looks for ever lean,"